1
00:00:15,833 --> 00:00:19,583
Of course, this was a mysterious secret for the prisoners

2
00:00:19,583 --> 00:00:22,208
We felt something unnatural in the prison

3
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:29,708
Whenever any door opened, the
humidity level rose in a strange way

4
00:00:29,750 --> 00:00:35,666
And in summer, the air became cold, and
very cold air came from the tunnel

5
00:00:35,666 --> 00:00:39,708
Of course, we didn’t know there was
a tunnel until the prison was bombed

6
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:41,125
There was shelling on the prison

7
00:00:41,125 --> 00:00:44,666
At that time, I had already been released, about a week earlier

8
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:47,458
Then Russian aircraft began bombing Burj Prison

9
00:00:48,125 --> 00:00:53,833
They took the Muslim prisoners, as they
considered them, down into the basement

10
00:00:54,125 --> 00:00:57,500
And the so-called infidel prisoners stayed in the main prison

11
00:00:57,500 --> 00:01:00,916
Meaning that even if it was bombed, it didn’t matter,
they could die, they were already as good as dead

12
00:01:00,916 --> 00:01:05,416
That’s when most of the prisoners
got to know each other in the basement

13
00:01:05,458 --> 00:01:07,166
They hadn’t known they were imprisoned together

14
00:01:07,166 --> 00:01:12,166
Of course, we left the basement because the humidity
level rose, and I started having trouble breathing

15
00:01:12,541 --> 00:01:14,083
We couldn’t stay any longer

16
00:01:14,791 --> 00:01:16,375
Because the humidity was extremely high

17
00:01:18,333 --> 00:01:22,958
I still don’t know how they used that tunnel
or how they kept the prisoners down there

18
00:01:23,583 --> 00:01:25,583
They even blindfolded them

19
00:01:25,625 --> 00:01:28,708
At first, when they brought them in, they were
blindfolded, then they removed the blindfolds

20
00:01:28,708 --> 00:01:32,750
And then they blindfolded them again—how those
prisoners endured and stayed alive, I don’t know
